es/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tejaye>Tejaye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 9:56:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why Do You Like Being A Mage...Do You Get Bored?</span><hr size=1> I was curious if any of you get bored since after reading all of your spells it seems they are mostly pet attack then nuke. It seems other classes get snares/fears/dots and nukes (plus heal and add mana) at same time. I think Mages could be a kewl alt for me, but I was curious if it gets very repititious?<br>
What do you all like best about the class?<br>
Under level 35.....are you just as strong as a Necro?<br>
It just seems for some reason VI cheats Mages out of some spells. I see Necros get heals/mez/root/dots/nukes (undead)/infravision.....all in addition to pet. Do you feel like VI cheats you?<br>
I wanted to get through these issues before I make the alt. Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 590<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 10:17:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why Do You Like Being A Mage...Do You Get Bored?</span><hr size=1> In the past I've watched druids do some soloing, how exciting is it to root a mob and watch it slowly die from DoTs? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Its actually not all that repititious when you think of the game as a whole (where true efficiency demands repitition). Our ability to summon 4 varieties of pets keeps things pretty fresh. <br>
<br>
When you start a spell circle your pets are generally very strong, as you get to the level just before the next circle you find yourself relying on nukes to keep your pet alive. <br>
<br>
The only drawback I've found in the 1-50 game is that people tend to confine yourself to a single hunting area for full set (or circle) of levels. But variety is out there if you know where to look.<br>
<br>
The whole inability to port thing isn't much of an issue if you have PoP, and that was probably the biggest drawback I had ever seen with this class (aside from a lack of true mana regen).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
