</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fashionmagician>FashionMagician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 11:39:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why Do You Like Being A Mage...Do You Get Bored?</span><hr size=1> All classes have boring repetition..<br>
<br>
Cleric= Heal med heal med heal nuke med med repeat<br>
<br>
Warrior= Hit Hit Kick Hit Hit Hit Kick CRITHIT Hit Hit *Cheer my destructive uberness*<br>
<br>
Ranger= Run back to corpse, run back to corpse, level alt a bit, run back to corpse...<br>
<br>
Its all in how you PLAY the game.. if your just a leveling machine, then yes.. I imagine it would get very boring, nomatter what class you play.<br>
<br>
(and yes I have a ranger alt =P)<br>
