 <p><B>Zress</B> <BR>
<B>Fashion Magician</B> <BR> <I> <B>"((POOF!)) Your in style!"</I> </B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tejaye>Tejaye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(11/21/02 11:49:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pets</span><hr size=1> Speaking of pets. Under what conditions or what mobs, under level 30...When SOLO...would you use the Air Pet, I hear he is weak. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fenobleu@themagicianstower>Fenobleu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 12:07:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why a Mage is Interesting to Me</span><hr size=1> From personal experience I would agree that a Mage (at least up until level 44) has far fewer bells and whistles than a Druid, Bard, or Necro.   Having relatively few tools requires a Mage to be extremely proficient and creative with those tools to be successful.    Mana efficiency, pet selection, mage to pet aggro transference, chaincasting, and spawn breaking are some of the many skills that a Mage has to  master to survive.   After 44 levels I feel far from having mastered the class and for me that is what keeps it interesting.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368916">Fenobleu Wayfarer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
44th level Mage, Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzabarr@themagicianstower>Azzabarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 12:18:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   why interesting?</span><hr size=1> There is less variety in terms of types of spells, but that is not the same as inherrent boredom.  Warriors don't get ANY spells but can be real fun, for example.  One thing mages get is the ability to pretty much kick butt...we are fiends at outputting dmg, and can often handle adds when soloing by simply blowing the head off of the initial mob withen a few seconds.  Other solo classes can't do that without going Oom all the time.  It's a bit simpler in terms of how many buttons you have to push to kill each mob, which is good or bad depending on how you like to play.  The class used to be sort of unrewarding at end-game situations at times, but perhaps in the PoP era mages are plenty fun at more end-game stuff, since more of it revolves around quick, damage intensive battles, which mages are excellent at. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 591<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 1:52:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why interesting?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Speaking of pets. Under what conditions or what mobs, under level 30...When SOLO...would you use the Air Pet, I hear he is weak. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Air pets excel against caster mobs due to their stun. They also do fare better against slow but hard hitting mobs, as they mitigate dmg better than the other pets.<br>
<br>
Earth pet has the most hp, and does work well if you are fighting rootable mobs and have a lot of potential for adds, but the root spell causes them to take a very large pounding at the end of a fight, and our heal spells aren't very mana efficient to make up for that.<br>
<br>
Fire pets excel against the quick hitting mobs (check out the needlites in echo caverns for the great example).<br>
<br>
Water is great in groups as it can do the most offensive damage, I really never used it much &lt;50 when soloing, as there was usually a better choice from the other three.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 55th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 4:03:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why interesting?</span><hr size=1> I get bored sometimes... and other times it's a real kick to be a magician.<br>
<br>
My greatest excitement comes from discovering new tactics, solo and grouped... and expanding my realm of usefulness.  It's the part of the game I love the most. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dolekinsoothesayer>Dolekin Soothesayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/phpBB2/images/avatars/gallery/Misc3/babykick.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 4:31:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why interesting?</span><hr size=1> I like a mage because I don't have a &quot;Definate&quot; role.  My role changes depending on the situation.  Mages, plain and simple, are multi-taskers.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sure I get bored, but that's why I don't play as much like I use too. <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;div align=left&gt;&lt;table width=&quot;270&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; bgcolor=&quot;000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;DIV style=&quot;FILTER: glow(color=FFFF00); WIDTH: 100%; POSITION: relative&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif&quot; size=&quot;5&quot; color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;I&gt;&lt;a style=&quot;font-weight:bold; color:#FFFF00; text-decoration: none&quot;href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43987 &gt;Dolekin Soothesayer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;DIV style=&quot;FILTER:  Blur(Add = 1,Direction=225, Strength=20); WIDTH: 100%; POSITION: relative&quot; align=center&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;1&quot; color=&quot;CCCCCC&quot;&gt;Gnomish Conjurer of the 58th Season&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr bgcolor=#dcdeed&gt;&lt;td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left&gt;<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stehle>stehle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 7:05:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why interesting?</span><hr size=1> I love the mage.  It is actually the reason I started eq.  My friend described the game and explained the different classes.  The idea of a mage (esp an epic mage) that could be so versatile was fascinating.  I like the fact that I can solo when I want to, or I can group.  I've &quot;trained&quot; all the people who I play with to love me and respect me for the damage output.  =)  Also, they have developed new strategies to incorporate my unique abilities into the group.  Perfect example, tonight in the Hole they wanted me to use an Air pet to stun the mob so there was less damage output (usually i'm a Water pet person).  Later when we went to Droga, I led the charge so my pet could eat any HT or nukes from the goblins.  I love it.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and when you hit 44... the whole world changes.  Your nukes and your pets all of a sudden allow you to do and solo things you never though possible...like solo RM by simply camping on top of the hill.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, it is also fun to show the parses of how your pet had higher damage output than the main tank (this is especially amusing when your pet quads for 48 pts of damage).<br>
<br>
It is a fun class.  You can play minimum risk or you can really try some cool strategies such as aggro-kiting or chain casting.  I love it.<br>
<br>
Casala, 47 mage (not for long!) of Saryn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iblisthemage>IblisTheMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 174<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 7:32:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.decara.com/eq/Federico6060.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: why interesting?</span><hr size=1> If you are healing pet, air is often a very good choice. It has somewhat lowish hp, but the good dammage mitigation gives you the most tanking pr heal. Remember to give it armour, jewelery, weapons, etc etc untill you fill all the slots =). Also str and ag bufs are good. If you know a high level mage, he can summon you the real good pet stuff, it will make a noticeable difference. Also aego and the like is good for little pets =).<br>
<br>
 <p>Iblis<br>
Archmage of the Heralds of Dawn<br>
Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=urgathbubblespawner>UrgathBubblespawner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 10:09:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pets</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Speaking of pets. Under what conditions or what mobs, under level 30...When SOLO...would you use the Air Pet, I hear he is weak.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I found the lvl 24ish (?) airpet so weak so I didn't use again until I was in the late 40s. <br>
The higher level Airpets are great but I didn't like em at all at lowlevels.<br>
I always prefered water or maybe earth when I was under 30.<br>
<br>
Playing a mage is fun and challenging, imo very far away from just sick the pet and nuke...<br>
<br>
