<br>
The main drawback is that the air pets damage output is much lower than the water pet's because of lower strength and no damage from the spell.  <br>
<br>
However, watching a caster mob be continually be stunned and not get a single spell off is sweet.  <br>
<br>
Basically, from 16 thru 20, if you are fighting only casters, the air pet is worth it, especially in a group where it won't be the main tank.  <br>
<br>
At 24 and 29th, when fighting mostly casters, go with the air pet.  Also, a group with minimal healing, the air pet is good.  The stun stops attacks as well and that can really reduce the amount of damage you tank takes and the pet can tank reasonably well.  In addition, the stun will interrupt the fleeing of mobs without having the side effects that rooting does.      <br>
<br>
The magicians pets vary widely across levels as well as types.  <br>
<br>
When getting your focus items, you have to fight the magicians in Najena.  Your 2xth level air pets work well here.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 6:45:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7933.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pets</span><hr size=1> Air pet becomes REALLY nice once you hit 53. &lt; 53, air has below average HP. &gt; 53, air has more HP than water, and the stun actually does damage! That's when you want air to be your primary pet as opposed to earth unless you're chainsummoning.<br>
<br>
(speaking of pre-50 pets now)<br>
<br>
In terms of raw damage, the majority of Fire's damage is through its DS. It has very low HP, so you have to work to keep it alive. But against fast hitting mobs, it literally shreds through them.<br>
